Reasoning: The paper discusses methods for analyzing and partitioning large temporal graphs, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on community detection and dynamic mesoscale description suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The use of optimal structural description and the relevance of the method for analyzing scientific networks suggest cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as possible sub-categories. The discussion of dynamic processes and the use of partitions for each time slice suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of network analysis and the relevance of the method for revealing evolutions in networks suggest cs.SN (Networking and Internet Architecture) as a possible sub-category.
